<TITLE> Hundreds of BDR staff 'unable' to report </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 1 (bdnews24.com)  Hundreds of civilian personnel working in various departments of BDR headquarters have not been able to report back to duty in line with a government order. The home ministry in a notice issued at 1:30pm Saturday ordered all BDR personnel, "absent form their posts in the wake of the quelled mutiny" to join their posts within the next 24 hours. The deadline ended Sunday afternoon. Border guards began reporting to stations from Saturday evening. Men in uniform gathered in Rifles Square outside the BDR headquarters and those without uniforms but holding ID cards reported at the Abahani Club grounds in Dhanmondi. "They (officials at the posts) are saying that since we are not soldiers they cannot register us," said Abdur Razzak, who works in the record wing at the BDR headquarters. The officials at the reporting stations could not say anything about the matter either, he added. The bewildered staff are worried as Saturday's order warned of legal consequences if they failed to report by the deadline. "The notice warns of legal actions but we are herewhat should we do now?" Habib, who worked with the finance department and gave only one name, told bdnews24.com. bdn
